Amine Bellachhab
With a strong mathematical background and a decade of enriching experience in education, I am confident that I possess the necessary skills and expertise to make a substantial contribution to the academic success of my students.
Throughout my teaching career, I have developed a deep understanding of mathematics and a passion for helping students achieve their full potential. I am committed to creating a dynamic and engaging learning environment that fosters critical thinking, problem-solving, and a love for mathematics. My teaching approach is student-centered and focused on meeting the individual needs of each student through personalized instruction and differentiated learning strategies.
In my current role as a Mathematics Teacher, I have successfully implemented innovative teaching practices, resulting in significant improvements in student performance and engagement. I am also a strong advocate for the use of technology in education and have experience integrating technology into the classroom to enhance learning outcomes.
Beyond my pedagogical prowess, I am adept at harnessing advanced educational technologies. Proficient in computer-assisted teaching software such as GeoGebra, Cabri 2D & 3D, MathType, Latex, and MathLab, I leverage these tools to deliver interactive and stimulating online courses. Additionally, I bring expertise in instructional design software, including Articulate 360 – Rise –, Microsoft Sway, Camtasia, and Moodle.

Finally, my familiarity with office software, including Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Google Meet, Zoom, and Microsoft Teams, facilitates seamless communication and online collaboration.
